title: Road closed due to fallen tree in Jersey | Channel
text:
A road in St Helier has been reopened after it was closed due to a tree blocking the road.
States of Jsy Police @JerseyPolice Follow There is currently a tree blocking the roundabout at Rouge Bouillon, the road is closed at the junction with Great Union Road / Roussell St
09:36 - 13 Oct 2015 Retweet Reply Favourite A one-lane closure was in place at Rouge Bouillon for vehicles heading from Great Union Road towards the roundabout, while a tree surgeon worked on removing the obstruction.
The road has since been cleared and reopened.
Last updated Tue 13 Oct 2015 Travel Jersey
